# Frontend Environment Variables

# ====================
# Backend API Configuration
# ====================
# Backend API URL (change to your deployed backend URL in production)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api

# ====================
# SECURITY - NOW IMPLEMENTED! ✅
# ====================
# The backend now handles all sensitive operations:
# ✅ Password hashing is done server-side with bcrypt (10 salt rounds)
# ✅ JWT tokens are generated and validated server-side
# ✅ Gemini API key is stored only on the server (never exposed to client)
# ✅ Rate limiting protects against brute force attacks
# ✅ Input validation with Zod schemas
# ✅ CORS protection configured
# ✅ SQL injection protection via Prisma ORM
#
# The frontend only needs to know the backend API URL.
# All sensitive data should be configured in server/.env

# ====================
# Development Setup
# ====================
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Start the backend server:
#    cd server
#    npm install
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit server/.env and add your GEMINI_API_KEY
#    npm run prisma:generate
#    npm run prisma:migrate
#    npm run dev
#
# 3. Start the frontend (in a new terminal):
#    cd ..
#    npm install
#    npm run dev
#
# 4. Access the application:
#    Frontend: http://localhost:3000
#    Backend:  http://localhost:3001
#    Health:   http://localhost:3001/health
#
# The frontend will automatically connect to the backend API.
